nt\":{\"status\":\"LIKE\",\"target\":{\"videoId\":\"TKgjq-Epaak\"},\"likeParams\":\"Cg0KC1RLZ2pxLUVwYWFrIAAyDAjigL7QBhDWqfGbAg%3D%3D\"}},\"idamTag\":\"66426\"}},\"trackingParams\":\"CIgCEPqGBCITCLWV58Wwy5QDFccpVQgddLwI6Q==\"}}}}}}}]}},\"accessibilityText\":\"fai clic su Mi piace su questo video come hanno fatto 61 altre persone\",\"style\":\"BUTTON_VIEW_MODEL_STYLE_MONO\",\"trackingParams\":\"CIcCEKVBIhMItZXnxbDLlAMVxylVCB10vAjp\",\"isFullWidth\":false,\"type\":\"BUTTON_VIEW_MODEL_TYPE_TONAL\",\"buttonSize\":\"BUTTON_VIEW_MODEL_SIZE_DEFAULT\",\"accessibilityId\":\"id.video.like.button\",\"tooltip\":\"Mi piace\"}},\"toggledButtonViewModel\":{\"buttonViewModel\":{\"iconName\":\"LIKE\",\"title\":\"62\",\"onTap\":{\"serialCommand\":{\"commands\":[{\"logGestureCommand\":{\"gestureType\":\"GESTURE_EVENT_TYPE_LOG_GENERIC_CLICK\",\"trackingParams\":\"CIYCE","finalUrl":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TKgjq-Epaak"}}},{"id":"q_aba886f8936f52614c","title":"Demis Hassabis on AI at Google I/O","shortDesc":"Google DeepMind CEO Demis Hassabis said AI progress is becoming tangible and discussed AGI and the singularity. The article also covers Google’s AI product announcements at I/O.","url":"https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/technology/tech-news/google-deepmind-ceo-demis-hassabis-remarks-on-ai-at-i/o-that-stunned-the-audience-this-year-we-can/articleshow/131245248.cms","addedAt":"2026-05-21T22:00:00.270Z","state":"approved","stateChangedAt":"2026-05-26T05:43:20.482Z","stateReason":"Approved for publishing from the dashboard.","selectionReason":"Timely Google I/O AI remarks and AGI framing from a major AI leader.","producerWorkerId":"core.news","itemType":"news.article","tags":["news"],"payload":{"digestRunId":"2026-05-21T22-00-00-270Z.json","source":{"host":"timesofindia.indiatimes.com","score":2,"label":"medium","reasons":["Article page extracted with substantial text."]},"article":{"fetched":true,"title":"Google DeepMind CEO Demis Hassabis'' remarks on AI at I/O that ''stunned'' the audience: This year, we can…","description":"Tech News News: Demis Hassabis closed Google I/O 2026 on Tuesday with a line that drew audible gasps from the room. The Google DeepMind CEO told developers they were .","excerpt":"Edition IN IN \n US \n GCC \n \n\n English English \n हिन्दी \n मराठी \n ಕನ್ನಡ \n தமிழ் \n বাংলা \n മലയാളം \n తెలుగు \n ગુજરાતી \n \n\n \n Weather \n\n \n \n \n Sign In \n\n TOI \n \n \n Today''s ePaper \n Live \n\n \n\n \n \n\n \n News \n Technology News \n Tech News \n Google DeepMind CEO Demis Hassabis'' remarks on AI at I/O that ''stunned'' the audience: This year, we can… \n \n Google DeepMind CEO Demis Hassabis'' remarks on AI at I/O that ''stunned'' the audience: This year, we can… \n\n TOI Tech Desk / TIMESOFINDIA.COM / May 21, 2026, 16:12 IST \n \n Comments\n Share \n\n AA + Text Size Small\n Medium\n Large\n \n\n \n \n\n Demis Hassabis, Co-Founder and CEO, Google DeepMind, speaks at a Google I/O event in Mountain View, Calif., Tuesday, May 19, 2026. (AP Photo/Jeff Chiu) \n\n \n \n\nDemis Hassabis closed Google I/O 2026 on Tuesday with a line that drew audible gasps from the room. The Google DeepMind CEO told developers they were \"standing in the foothills of the singularity\"—a phrasing the tech industry usually keeps to podcasts and late-night X threads, not main-stage keynotes. He doubled down the next day. Speaking to Axios at the developer conference, Hassabis said this is the year the shift starts becoming tangible. With the agentic systems shipping right now, he said, \"we can start feeling it now.\" His evidence was unusually personal. Hassabis said he''s been using AI agents to build mini video games late at night—projects that would have taken many months of engineering work just a few years ago. It''s the kind of compressed timeline that previously belonged to thought experiments. What Hassabis actually means when he says ''singularity'' \n\nThe singularity, as Vernor Vinge and Ray Kurzweil originally framed it, is the point where machine intelligence overtakes human intelligence and starts improving itself in a runaway loop. Hassabis uses the term more narrowly. For him, it''s roughly synonymous with the arrival of full AGI, which he pegs at a 50 percent likelihood by 2030—the same timeline he''s been citing in interviews for months. \n \n\n He isn''t predicting a machine takeover. Hassabis has described himself as a cautious optimist and said AI will be roughly 100 times more impactful than the Industrial Revolution, mostly through breakthroughs in science and healthcare. Why Sundar Pichai handed the I/O 2026 closing slot to Hassabis \n\nThe keynote setup itself was telling. Pichai typically delivers the closing remarks at I/O. This year he gave the final stretch to Hassabis, right after the unveiling of Gemini for Science—a research platform aimed at accelerating drug discovery and, eventually, helping cure disease. The two-hour address also covered the Gemini 3.5 model family, an upgraded coding assistant, new advertising formats for AI Mode in Search, and a fresh timeline for Google ''s smart glasses revival. But the closing was about framing the stakes. Hassabis called AGI the most profound technology ever invented and said DeepMind is now on the horizon of inventing it. \"We''re in a moment of immense promise, but also enormous responsibility,\" he said. It''s a sharp tonal pivot for Google, which has spent years describing AI in measured, product-shaped terms. On Tuesday, its top AI researcher picked a different register entirely—one that asks the room not just to use the products, but to think hard about what they''re building toward. \n\n \n\n \n\n About the Author TOI Tech Desk \n\n The TOI Tech Desk is a dedicated team of journalists committed to delivering the latest and most relevant news from the world of technology to readers of The Times of India. TOI Tech Desk’s news coverage spans a wide spectrum across gadget launches, gadget reviews, trends, in-depth analysis, exclusive reports and breaking stories that impact technology and the digital universe. Be it how-tos or the latest happenings in AI, cybersecurity, personal gadgets, platforms like WhatsApp, Instagram, Facebook and more; TOI Tech Desk brings the news with accuracy and authenticity. Read More \n\n \n\n End of Article \n \n\n \n Latest Mobiles\n\n View All \n Previous \n\n HMD Vibe 2 5G\n ₹8,999\n\n \n\n \n\n Motorola Razr Fold\n ₹1,49,999\n\n \n\n \n\n Ai+ Nova Flip\n ₹39,999\n\n \n\n \n\n OnePlus Nord CE 6 Lite 5G\n ₹31,999\n\n \n\n \n\n Moto G37 Power 5G\n \n\n \n\n \n\n Moto G37 5G\n \n\n \n\n \n\n Realme 50A Prime\n \n\n \n\n \n\n Poco C81x 4G\n ₹10,999\n\n \n\n \n\n OnePlus 10R Prime Blue Edition\n \n\n \n\n \n\n Infinix Hot 10 Play\n \n\n \n\n Next 1 \n 2 \n 3 \n 4 \n 5 \n 6 \n \n\n Follow Us On Social Media \n\n Photostories \n\n \n\n \n Sattu Sharbat to Milk with Sugar: Ministry of Ayush recommends general food measures to fight heatwave \n\n \n\n \n Big boost for commuters: 1st girder installed on Mumbai freeway’s Chedda–Anand Nagar stretch; what we know \n\n \n\n \n Personality test: Antique, round, or table with drawer? The furniture you choose reveals if your views are traditional, balanced or practical towards life \n\n \n\n \n 10 hottest places in India today and things travellers should know before visiting \n\n \n\n \n From London to Miami: Exploring David Beckham’s most luxurious homes and their massive worth \n\n \n\n \n ‘Mudhalvan’ to ‘Singam’: When Thalapathy Vijay said NO to these blockbuster films \n\n \n\n \n 5 most beautiful Forget- me- not varieties to add colour to your garden \n\n \n\n \n Best plants to grow in India before the monsoon arrives \n\n \n\n \n 8 Indian villages that feel straight out of a fairytale and are perfect for a slow travel escape \n\n \n\n \n 5 smart ways to arrange your kitchen so it looks spacious \n\n 1 \n 2 \n 3 \n \n\n Hot Picks \n Bandra demolition drive \n\n US Iran war \n\n Indian rupee \n\n Gold rate today 